==Demographics==
Rio first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2020 U.S. census]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020 Geography Changes|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/acs/technical-documentation/table-and-geography-changes/2020/geography-changes.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=}}</ref>

The population at the 2020 census was 2,076.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://data.tennessean.com/census/total-population/total-population-change/rio-cdp-virginia/160-5167288/ | title=Rio CDP, Virginia Demographics and Housing 2020 Decennial Census }}</ref>

